How did you combine multiple files in Linux?
 To combine multiple files you type bash$ cat file1.txt file2.txt file3.txt file4.txt > mergedfile.txt into your terminal
How can you split multiple files in Linux?
To split multiple files you have to type split --bytes=1M /path/to/image/image.jpg /path/to/image/prefixForNewImagePieces
Hint: there is a way with a very basic command. 
